g.aria-label: 1. Object is too small Choose an other stitch type like f.e. running stitch or make your shape a little bit bigger (or delete). 2. No embroiderable path Convert your shape into a path through "Path > Object to path" (Ctrl Shift C). Shapes with holes are possible. 3. Nodes are too close / onto each other In node editor mode, break your path apart and connect open ends the other way around. 4. Path is overlapping Use "Path > Union" (Ctrl +) and then "Path > Break apart" (Ctrl Shift K) two receive to individual objects. 5. Path consists of two not connected shapes Run "Path > Break apart" (Ctrl Shift K) to receive two individual objects.

use.inkscape:label: Ink/Stitch Command: Ignore layer (do not stitch any objects in this layer)
